# .gitattributes — line ending and binary file handling for otto-gateway.
#
# Why this exists: developers work on macOS + Windows laptops (see DEVELOPERS.md).
# Without per-pattern normalization, Windows Git's core.autocrlf=true silently
# converts .sh and Makefile to CRLF on checkout, which breaks bash interpreter
# lookup, gofmt, and tab-significant Makefiles.

# Default: detect text vs binary; normalize text to LF in repo, render
# platform-native on checkout.
* text=auto

# Shell scripts MUST stay LF — bash refuses CRLF in shebang parsing.
*.sh text eol=lf

# PowerShell: leave to auto. PowerShell handles either; platform-native is
# friendliest (Windows checkout → CRLF, macOS/Linux → LF).

# Go: gofmt enforces LF. Pin it so a CRLF commit can't sneak through.
*.go text eol=lf
go.mod text eol=lf
go.sum text eol=lf

# Make is tab-significant and brittle on CRLF.
Makefile text eol=lf

# Config formats: LF in repo (some parsers are strict, CI tools historically
# broke on CRLF).
*.yml text eol=lf
*.yaml text eol=lf
*.json text eol=lf
.editorconfig text eol=lf
.golangci.yml text eol=lf
.pre-commit-config.yaml text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
